{
  "text": "Because of the relatively prolonged preconditioning ischemic stimulus used in the study by Cai and Semenza, [CITATION_1] we have to question whether the phenomenon of IPC was actually investigated. It would be important to establish whether a standard IPC protocol comprising 5 minutes of myocardial ischemia and reperfusion for the isolated perfused rat heart would have had the same effects on PTEN activity observed with the prolonged 15 minutes of ischemia used in this study.",
